GEMINI-CLI(1)              User Commands              GEMINI-CLI(1)

NAME
    gemini-cli - bash-only terminal interface for the Gemini API

SYNOPSIS
    gemini-cli
    gemini-cli <session_name>
    gemini-cli --resume <session_name>
    gemini-cli --list
    gemini-cli --models
    gemini-cli --update-models
    gemini-cli --select-model
    gemini-cli --test-model <model_id>
    gemini-cli --attach <file> [session_name]
    gemini-cli --set-api-key
    gemini-cli --config
    gemini-cli --set <key> <value>
    gemini-cli --unset <key>
    gemini-cli --credits
    gemini-cli --version
    gemini-cli --help

DESCRIPTION
    The bash-only gemini-cli is the dependency-light shell implementation of
    gemini-terminal-tools.

    It avoids Python while still aiming to be an end-user Gemini terminal chat
    client rather than a curl example.

    It provides:
        - interactive chat loop
        - persistent sessions
        - named and resumable sessions
        - model discovery
        - model cache
        - model selection
        - model testing
        - config file support
        - rolling conversation context
        - human-readable logs
        - startup Project Lead notice
        - basic text/media attachment support

USAGE
    First-time setup:

        gemini-cli --set-api-key
        gemini-cli --update-models
        gemini-cli --select-model

    Start a new session:

        gemini-cli

    Start or reopen a named session:

        gemini-cli android-backup

    Attach a file to the next message:

        gemini-cli --attach notes.txt android-backup

INPUT
    Type or paste a message, then press Ctrl+D to send.

DEPENDENCIES
    Required:
        bash, curl, awk, sed, grep, tr, mktemp, base64

    Optional:
        jq

    If jq is installed, JSON parsing and model metadata handling are stronger.
    Without jq, the script uses best-effort awk/sed parsing.

CONFIGURATION
    Config file:

        ~/.config/gemini-cli/config

    Supported keys include:

        MODEL
        CONTEXT_TURNS
        GEMINI_API_KEY
        SESSION_DIR
        ATTACHMENT_DIR
        MODEL_TEST_PROMPT
        STARTUP_NOTICE
        MAX_ATTACHMENT_BYTES
        MODEL_CACHE_FILE
        MODEL_FILTER_GENERATE_CONTENT
        MODEL_FILTER_REQUIRE_TOKENS
        MODEL_FILTER_HIDE_PREVIEW
        MODEL_MIN_INPUT_TOKENS
        MODEL_MIN_OUTPUT_TOKENS
        MODEL_SORT_ORDER

MODEL DISCOVERY
    Update model cache:

        gemini-cli --update-models

    List models:

        gemini-cli --models

    The raw Gemini model-list endpoint is:

        https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta/models?key=YOUR_API_KEY

MODEL TESTING
    Test one selected model:

        gemini-cli --test-model gemini-2.5-flash

    This edition does not autoscan/probe every model.

ATTACHMENTS
    Text-like files are inserted as text parts.

    Binary/media files are sent as inlineData when possible. This requires
    base64 and depends on Gemini model/API support.

LIMITATIONS
    - Avoids Python by design
    - jq is optional but improves JSON handling
    - No full-screen UI
    - No mouse support
    - JSON parsing without jq is best-effort
    - Media attachment support depends on selected model and API behavior

VERSION
    gemini-cli bash-only version 0.1.0

